        {
            "author_association": "NONE",
            "body": "Just as a follow up. What I personally would like to use it for is\r\n\r\n- as a scrollbar with mouse support which would then also serve as an indicator how big the file is and at which place in the file I am currently located\r\n- as an indicator  for example for where and how many highlighted search-results/warnings/errors/githunks from other plugins exist\r\n\r\nPreferably both at the same time. I feel like this is something I am missing the most from guis because it helps me a lot to get a sense of the structure of the file and to explore new files.\r\n\r\nAn example can be seen in the image where githunks and search-results and their location in their file can be seen on the right side within the scrollbar.\r\n\r\n![2019-10-17-115350_919x1059_scrot](https://user-images.githubusercontent.com/36510152/66998773-1e62c300-f0d5-11e9-8e30-08127c945256.png)\r\n",
